The paper deals with the analysis of recurrence relations induced by randomized algorithms, which is a topic closely related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The focus on obtaining efficient bounds also suggests numerical analysis (cs.NA) as a likely sub-category. The use of algorithms to derive these bounds suggests discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the implementation aspect of the paper suggests programming languages (cs.PL) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
